wdi-IQ.SCI.MTHD.def: The methodology indicator measures a country’s ability to adhere to internationally recommended standards and methods. The methodology score is calculated as the weighted average of 10 underlying indicator scores. The final methodology score contributes 1/3 of the overall Statistical Capacity Indicator score.
wdi-IQ.SCI.MTHD.name: Methodology assessment of statistical capacity
wdi-IQ.SCI.MTHD.source: World Bank, Bulletin Board on Statistical Capacity (http://bbsc.worldbank.org).
